 ...}\n```\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v1/bots` | GET | List all bots (non-discarded) |\n| `/api/v1/bots` | POST | Create new bot (pending status) |\n| `/api/v1/bots/:id` | GET | Bot detail + recent trades |\n| `/api/v1/bots/:id` | PATCH | Update status, risk params |\n| `/api/v1/bots/:id` | DELETE | Discard bot |\n| `/api/v1/bots/:id/grid` | GET | Grid levels with order status |\n| `/api/v1/bots/:id/trades` | GET | Paginated trade history |\n| `/api/v1/bots/:id/chart` | GET | Balance snapshots for charting |\n| `/api/v1/exchange/pairs` | GET | Available trading pairs |\n| `/api/v1/exchange/balance` | GET | Current account balance |\n\n### ActionCable Messages\n\n| Source | Message Type | Payload |\n|---|---|---|\n| OrderFillWorker | `fill` | grid_level, trade, realized_profit, trade_count |\n| BalanceSnapshotWorker | `price_update` | current_price, unrealized_pnl, total_value_quote |\n| RiskManager | `status` | status, trigger_price |\n| RiskManager | `risk_error` | message |\n\n---\n\n## 6. System Architecture Summary\n\n| Component | Role | Latency |\n|---|---|---|\n| **WebSocket Listener** (`bin/ws_listener`) | Detects fills instantly | < 100ms |\n| **OrderFillWorker** (Sidekiq critical) | Places counter-orders, records trades | < 500ms |\n| **ReconciliationWorker** (Sidekiq default) | Catches missed fills, repairs gaps | 15s interval |\n| **BalanceSnapshotWorker** (Sidekiq cron) | Tracks portfolio value over time | 5min interval |\n| **DCP (Dead Man's Switch)** | Exchange cancels all orders if bot dies | 40s timeout |\n| **ActionCable** | Pushes real-time updates to frontend | Instant |\n| **Redis** | Hot cache for dashboard reads | Sub-ms |\n\n---\n\n## 7. The Profit Mechanism\n\n```\nPrice range: $2400 - $2600, 10 levels, step = $20\n\nLevel 10: $2600 SELL ←───┐\nLevel  9: $2580 SELL      │ Sell fills → place buy below\nLevel  8: $2560 SELL      │ profit = step x qty - fees\nLevel  7: $2540 (skip)    │\nLeve